docs.abstract: Accelerating growth has given the administration more leverage over trading partners. But economists warn of potential headwinds beyond this year.

docs.lead_paragraph: The American economy has picked up speed and is now on course to expand this year at the fastest rate in more than a decade. That acceleration gives President Trump a stronger hand as he contemplates more tariffs and takes an increasingly confrontational approach with China, Canada, Mexico and other trading partners.

docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — On his first day as the owner of The Los Angeles Times, the billionaire biotech executive Dr. Patrick Soon-Shiong, hoping to bring stability to a newsroom bruised in recent years by steep staffing cuts and tumultuous leadership changes, named Norman Pearlstine as the newspaper’s top editor.
